Hello All,


Greetings from iBot and Electronics Club,


We are back with the Second Session of the Semester.

Ever had the desire to control a bot without actually trailing behind it?
Ever felt the issue of entangling wires while working?

You don't need to worry about them anymore.

In the previous workshop we built the Robots with a destructive mechanism,
this workshop will be on how do you automate them.

CFI invites you to, Come and explore the world of microcontrollers and
start with the basics of Arduino coding.


Venue: ESB 127, 128

Date: 1st November, 2016 (Tuesday)

Time: 7:30 p.m onward



PS: Have your dinner and come as it may extend beyond 9 p.m

Prerequisites:
Please carry your own Arduino which is a part of the kit provided in the
first workshop.

Laptop installed with the Arduino  IDE
and the drivers  for Arduino. Make
sure your laptop is fully charged.


The session is open to Everyone.



